HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 198
BY REPRESENTATIVE BOYER
A RESOLUTION
To commend Karaline Elizabeth Leblanc for being named the 2026 Breaux Bridge Crawfish
Festival Queen.
WHEREAS, it is fitting to recognize Karaline Elizabeth Leblanc for her
achievements and to commend her for being named the 2026 Breaux Bridge Crawfish
Festival Queen; and
WHEREAS, Karaline is the nineteen-year-old daughter of Kelly and Bryce Leblanc;
with the support of her parents, she has grown into a strong and confident young woman who
beautifully reflects the heart, culture, and traditions of the Breaux Bridge community; and
WHEREAS, Karaline is pursuing her passion for the beauty industry at the
Cosmetology Training Center of Lafayette, and she is dedicated to perfecting her craft while
building a career centered on helping others feel beautiful and confident; and
WHEREAS, Karaline strives to make a positive impact within her community and
beyond; as the Crawfish Festival Queen, she strongly supports efforts to get younger
generations involved and interested in the festival, and she works to preserve the traditions
and culture of Breaux Bridge by inspiring youth to take pride in their heritage and actively
participate in local events; and
WHEREAS, Karaline is excited to celebrate Breaux Bridge's unique and rich Cajun
heritage, music, food, and traditions; she proudly embraces her role as the ambassador of the
Breaux Bridge Crawfish Festival; and
WHEREAS, Karaline Elizabeth Leblanc is deserving of recognition for her
outstanding efforts to support and preserve the rich Cajun culture and heritage of Breaux
Bridge.
